verbose_text: RhoA activation in the presence of overexpressed Ephexin5 E/E-myc recapitulated but failed to surpass wild-type levels, suggesting that although glutamic acid substitution of Ephexin5 serines 107 and 109 can positively regulate Ephexin5 activity, this construct is likely an imperfect mimetic of the natively phosphorylated protein.
evidence: RhoA activation in the presence of overexpressed Ephexin5 E/E-myc
